metadata.name: Epiphany
metadata.description:
We are people of the 4th millennium.
Humanity is no longer the same as before.
We are the ones who stayed here- half humans, half code (program).
Our skin glows like a silicon wafer.
We almost destroyed nature on Earth, but there are still growing flowers somewhere.
And these flowers became a modern cult, an obsession, animal passion.

People are the Gods who created the new world,
but the Gods above people are nature.
Flowers are the only thing that the Earth still gives to humanity.
Humans go crazy when they see flowers, smell them, taste them, dance with them, touch them, admire them...
_

35 mm film 
Zenit- E: Kodak Vision200
